Short description of female paratypes .
Mostly same as males, colour slightly lighter, carapace length approximately equal to breadth or slightly longer than broad (0.99–1.06 ×). Galea with five short terminal branches. Female genitalia: anterior genital operculum with 14–16 simple and acuminate setae, 10–13 setae in a row along the posterior margin of the posterior operculum ( Fig. 2f ). Spermathecae (
Fig. 3g
) with two short tubules, each with a distinct terminal bulb; egg capsule (
Fig. 2i
) with 7–11 embryos.
